{"id": "EUVD-2022-55128", "enisaUuid": "12deb2cd-1445-3657-bf65-80221f667f5d", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nRDMA/hfi1: Fix use-after-free bug for mm struct\n\nUnder certain conditions, such as MPI_Abort, the hfi1 cleanup code may\nrepresent the last reference held on the task mm.\nhfi1_mmu_rb_unregister() then drops the last reference and the mm is freed\nbefore the final use in hfi1_release_user_pages().  A new task may\nallocate the mm structure while it is still being used, resulting in\nproblems. One manifestation is corruption of the mmap_sem counter leading\nto a hang in down_write().  Another is corruption of an mm struct that is\nin use by another task.", "datePublished": "2025-02-27T21:32:10", "dateUpdated": "2025-02-27T21:32:10", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5f54364ff6cfcd14cddf5441c4a490bb28dd69f7", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9ca11bd8222a612de0d2f54d050bfcf61ae2883f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0b7186d657ee55e2cdefae498f07d5c1961e8023", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5a9a1b24ddb510715f8f621263938186579a965c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2bbac98d0930e8161b1957dc0ec99de39ade1b3c", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49076"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49076"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "028804db-6c2b-3eab-8be6-7e712f236688", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3d2a9d642512c21a12d19b9250e7a835dcb41a79 <0b7186d657ee55e2cdefae498f07d5c1961e8023"}, {"id": "10ca3ca3-da60-3958-b296-d123e072c986", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.34"}, {"id": "156cb3da-2c1a-3015-afc7-7bcf9ab7cc7a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3d2a9d642512c21a12d19b9250e7a835dcb41a79 <5f54364ff6cfcd14cddf5441c4a490bb28dd69f7"}, {"id": "2787ea12-3708-3b8d-b2bf-e65a4e3f3d70", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.111"}, {"id": "51fc0bfe-fa38-328f-9a0f-40feca6b9545"